## Usage Example

Here's a basic usage example of the `DataTableRowActions`:

```tsx
<Canvas>
  <Story name="Default">
    <DataTableRowActions
      row={{
        original: {
          id: "tx-123",
          date: "2023-05-15",
          description: "Office Supplies",
          amount: "$245.50",
          category: "Expenses",
          status: "Completed"
        }
      }}
      actions={[
        { 
          label: "Edit", 
          icon: "PencilIcon", 
          onClick: (row) => console.info("Edit transaction:", row) 
        },
        { 
          label: "Delete", 
          icon: "TrashIcon", 
          onClick: (row) => console.info("Delete transaction:", row),
          danger: true
        },
        { 
          label: "View Details", 
          icon: "EyeIcon", 
          onClick: (row) => console.info("View transaction details:", row) 
        }
      ]}
      className="p-2"
    />
  </Story>
</Canvas>
``` 